{"id":"cell--wcih7-mlhj5mb1j8c","title":"Rewrite ArylicVolumeClient from HTTP to TCP API (port 8899)","description":"The Arylic device's HTTP API (port 80) is not available. The TCP API on port 8899 works and has been verified. Rewrite the entire Arylic transport layer from HTTP/URLSession to TCP sockets using Network.framework (NWConnection). The TCP protocol uses a binary packet format: 4-byte header (18 96 18 20) + 4-byte LE length + 4-byte LE checksum + 8 zero bytes + ASCII payload. Commands: MCU+VOL+GET, MCU+MUT+GET, MCU+VOL+NNN, MCU+MUT+001/000. Responses: AXX+VOL+NNN, AXX+MUT+NNN (same binary wrapping). Volume range 0-100 (zero-padded 3 chars). Set commands return no response. The protocol interface (ArylicVolumeClientProtocol) remains unchanged.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-11T04:28:59.053Z","updated_at":"2026-02-11T04:28:59.053Z","dependencies":[],"labels":[],"comments":[]}
